# Manual Steps

k8s-forge intentionally leaves platform installation and runtime operations to the learner or operator.

Manual work includes:

- install ingress-nginx when Ingress is part of the lab;
- install cert-manager when certificate automation is part of the lab;
- install Linkerd before expecting service mesh behavior;
- install Kyverno before relying on runtime admission policy;
- install ArgoCD before expecting GitOps reconciliation;
- install Prometheus and Grafana before metrics dashboards are useful;
- install Loki and a compatible collector before logs are queryable;
- install Tempo and OpenTelemetry Collector before traces are queryable;
- run Terraform workflows manually outside k8s-forge;
- run Ansible workflows manually outside k8s-forge;
- run image scan and SBOM workflows manually when needed;
- provide real sensitive values through an external process;
- push code or workflow files manually after review;
- design production deployment as a separate controlled process.

This file is a checklist of responsibilities. It is not an execution plan.
